    <datafield ind1="C" ind2="5" tag="999">
      <subfield code="m">The sample holder consists of two concentric 1-mm-thick quartz unpolished cylinders inner diameters of 4 and 9 mm, respectively, length of 54 mm fixed on one end to a quartz injector equipped with a plano-convex lens and at the other end to a quartz reflector Light, inserted from a 05-mm optical fiber, is transported across the cylinder and is scattered laterally to irradiate as much of the sample as possible A g fine-powder sample is placed in the void between the cylinders The irradiated surface area is about 3000 and we estimate that the areal light power may be as high as 013 at a nominal source power of mW The ensemble, once mounted, is then capped and kept in place by an aluminum socket sealed to a copper block A similar setup is used in the diffraction experiment except that we use instead a single glass tube wrapped around the optic fiber with a g powder sample placed around it The irradiated surface area is about 430 with mW In no instance did the sample suffer from light damage</subfield>
